	//Bark Basket Entries
	"block-handbooktitle-barkbasket": "",
	"block-handbooktext-barkbasket": "<font align='center'><i>With each weave of the bark, 
we are closer to home.</i></font>
	<font weight='bold' align='center'>- On Basket Weaving</font>

	<font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font>

	These baskets are made wrought from the <a href=\"handbook://item-indappledgroves:bark-birch-soaked\">soaked bark</a> of any tree.  This timeless technology has survived the rot, and is a cornerstone of Seraph's looking for convenient storage.
					
	Bark has a long history of being used for the making of baskets in areas all over the world. Evidence of baskets can be found in cultures ranging from the Sami of the Sapmi region, the Salsih, Chilkat, and other Native American Tribes of the American Northwest, and countless others.",
	
	"barkbasketname": "Bark Baskets",
	"block-barkbasket": "Bark Basket",
	"barkbasketcontents": "Bark Basket",

	//Chopping Block Entries
	"block-handbooktitle-choppingblock": "How To Create:",	
	"block-handbooktext-choppingblock": "	<strong>Recipe Type:</strong> <a href=\"handbook://inworldcrafting-indappledgroves\">In World</a>
	<strong>Tool Mode:</strong> <a href=\"handbook://inworldcrafting-indappledgroves\">Hewing</a>
	<strong>Ingredients</strong>: <a href=\"handbook://block-indappledgroves:logslab-birch-barked-down-free\">Any log slab</a>
	<strong>Tools</strong>: <a href=\"handbook://item-indappledgroves:adze-wood-flint\">Adze</a>, <a href=\"handbook://item-indappledgroves:grubaxe-tinbronze\">Grub Axe</a>
",
	"block-handbooktitle-choppingblock2": "																			A Woodsman's Best Friend",
	"block-handbooktext-choppingblock2": "
	<font align='center'><i>Before Enlightenment -
	Chop Wood, Carry Water,
	After Enlightenment-
	Chop Wood, Carry Water</i></font>
	<font weight='bold' align='center'>- Zen Proverb </font>

				<font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#4ba328'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#065e30'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#E98604'><icon name=tree></icon></font><font color='#795825'><icon name=tree></icon></font>

			Made by laying any log slab flat on the ground, and <a href=\"handbook://inworldcrafting-indappledgroves\">hewing</a> it with an adze or other hewing tool, chopping blocks are the foundation of the serious woodsmans set of workstations. 
								 
			This workstation provides an improvement in the effectiveness of your tools. Work performed on a chopping block is generally faster than on the ground.

			In addition, there may be certain recipes that can only be performed with the help of a chopping block. For those intending to work with large amounts of wood, it should be the first workstation you acquire. 
",
	"block-choppingblock": "Chopping Block",
	
